<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0756 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is argued that there is no need, based on demand, for the Torness AGRstation to be commissioned. The costs of going ahead with the operationof the reactor are compared with the cost of mothballing the plant. Thecosts considered include the effect on the Scottish mining industry andthe problem of dealing with the radioactive wastes it will generate.However, both options will cost money. Continuing will increase the costof electricity by about 35%. Mothballing will also increase the costs.</TEXT></DOC>